Package models

Class ApiCallImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • models.ApiCallImpl
  • public class ApiCallImpl
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents API Calls. It consists of static methods which interacts with third party Api. It contains fields like apikey which is used for authentication of the api and a cache object in which the data is stored after making api calls to avoid repeated calls for same symbol. It also contains a error message which is returned when a api call fails.

      • getData

        public static float getData​(java.lang.String stockSymbol,
                            java.time.LocalDate date)
                     throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        This method takes in Symbol of a company and date on which the share price is required and returns the share value as a float. It checks in the cache first, if the symbol is not found in cache only then it makes api call.
        Parameters:
        stockSymbol - unique symbol of a company.
        date - the date in string format to get the share value
        Returns:
        returns a float which is the share value of that company on a particular date.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
